            },
            "reviewBody": "Made them with leftover chicken parmesan and they were great! The kids loved them. I will definitely make them again."
        },
        {
            "@type": "Review",
            "author": {
                "@type": "Person",
                "name": "Rick"
            },
            "reviewBody": "I make them with 2 tortillas and bake as hot as my oven gets for 8 minutes. No need to preheat the pan, just the oven. Small tortillas in a 9 inch pan, large burrito size in a 12 inch pan. Since there is a double layer I can load it up and it will take all the toppings without collapsing. I like sliced tomato, mushrooms, sausage, basil and cheese."
        },
        {
            "@type": "Review",
            "author": {
                "@type": "Person",
                "name": "Joan"
            },
            "reviewBody": "I have been making pizzas with tortillas for years now. I love thin, crispy crusts. Plus it is so easy &#38; quick to make in a toaster oven. My favorite is ham &#38; barbeque pizza, where I spread barbeque sauce, instead of pizza sauce, over the tortilla, then put some cut up lunch ham (or leftover ham) &#38; sprinkle with mozarella cheese. But I have also made tortilla pizzas with pizza sauce &#38; put a small amount of meat &#38; some veggies on it with cheese. All kinds of varieties!"
        },
